title: Neill Sheridan: Ex-outfielder was known for his 613-foot home run
text:
Photo: Michael Macor, The Chronicle Neill Sheridan with the ball and bat that he hit a 613-foot home run with back in 1953, at his granddaughter’s home in Antioch. Neill Sheridan with the ball and bat that he hit a 613-foot home...
Neill Sheridan, an outfielder in the old Pacific Coast League who supposedly hit the longest home run in history, died Thursday in Antioch. He was 93.
